<br>
When you turn in the seal to scout in perma the Icebound Spirit spawns, which is just another bear in the bear pits. The Icebound Spirit hits for 225 is immune to slow, high MR low FR, high CR. Once it dies you loot totem and bring it back to scout. Scout gives you the seal of khati sha back and the wrapped totem.<br>
<br>
So.. the next part would obviously be the other scouts. More info as it hits the presses. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uteramenor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Teramenor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/4/02 4:47:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3584.topic&index=143>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: BST epic</span><hr size=1> On Test Server, there are scouts in Lfay and the Feerrott.<br>
<br>
In Lfay, the scout is on the east wall, about a thousand feet south of the Steamfont zone. When the Beastlord hands him the Official Seal of the Khati Sha, &quot;The Spirit of Malevolence&quot; spawns a ways to the west. The Spirit is a gigantic white wolf. Not particularly hard to kill; has a lot of HP but only hits for around 200. However he procs a blindness spell.<br>
<br>
In Feerrott, the scout is just east of the druid rings. When the Beastlord hands him the Seal, a gigantic yellow spider called The Spirit of Decay spawns nearby. The spider is more or less the same difficulty as the wolf, except that the spider casts an AE snare DoT.<br>
<br>
We did both of these this weekend with 2 groups of 50+. Nobody died, it was easy; 1 group of 60s could do it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucarverfastrunner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Carver Fastrunner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/5/02 11:47:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3584.topic&index=144>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: BST epic</span><hr size=1> Teramenor : Does that mean someone on test is close to completeing the epic?  If so, how close? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uvegaslife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VegasLife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 8:32:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3584.topic&index=145>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> BST Epic</span><hr size=1> No one knows for sure if collecting the six pieces will end the quest or activate another part.  Hope to find out soon. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=3584.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=3584.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=3584.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=3584.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafeho